# Playwright Rules

- Responsibility: browser automation only (login, navigate, click, read, type)
- No business logic, filtering, AI, or scheduling decisions
- Prefer **Locator API**; avoid XPath
- Configurable timeouts via env; no hardcoded magic numbers scattered in code
- **No fixed `waitForTimeout` for flow control** — wait for conditions/locators
- Use random human-like delays only where intentional (apply pacing)
- Retries for flaky UI actions (bounded)
- Capture screenshot + page HTML snippet on failure
- One action module per domain area (auth, vacancies, chat, resume)

## Example

```typescript
// ❌ BAD
await page.waitForTimeout(5000);
await page.$x('//button[@id="apply"]');

// ✅ GOOD
await page.getByRole('button', { name: /откликнуться/i }).click();
```
